--- !u!1001 &7339643683790193295
PrefabInstance:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  serializedVersion: 2
  m_Modification:
    serializedVersion: 3
    m_TransformParent: {fileID: 2438202165021446829}
    m_Modifications:
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[0].text
      value: Well, this looks promising...
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[1].text
      value: 'It doesn''t <b><color=#FFD700>look.</color></b> That''s the point!
        It''s the power of the <b><color=#FFD700>unseen. </color></b>  '
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[2].text
      value: See, the door was blocking the cat, but now it's in <b><color=#FFD700>superposition.
        </color></b>
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[3].text
      value: 'And the cat now <b><color=#FFD700>both is blocked and not blocked </color></b> '
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[4].text
      value: If the cat can press <b><color=#FFD700>both butttons</color></b> to
        open the door... We'll know the experiment is a success <b><color=#FFD700>when
        the lights come back on. </color></b>
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2950478657829309437, guid: 37d31eb3b846be6439ed2769f9acd9e7, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogueLines.Array.data[0].speakerImage
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 141846719731478547, guid: 1a0fe95ac64a03447b25120a75c8d8d6, type: 3}
